President Uhuru Kenyatta yesterday directed the Ministry of Interior to provide a comprehensive policy framework that will address the persistent housing problems for the police. The head of state gave Interior Cabinet Secretary Fred Matiang’i(pictured) and Inspector General of Police Joseph Boinnet 30 days to give recommendations for improving efficiency in the service. Uhuru spoke at State House Nairobi where he conferred 47 police officers with the prestigious Head of State Commendation for gallant service.. Deputy President William Ruto attended the event. Uhuru said were it not for the bravery of the officers, many Kenyans would have lost their lives. “Your sacrifice, courage and bravery in serving this country are your greatest contribution to the prosperity of this country,” the President said. He applauded the National Police Service for its role in maintaining peace and stability during the last general election. Uhuru said the state would continue accelerated investments in the service to ensure police work effectively and delivery their mandate to Kenyans. The President said the state had increased its investment to the service from Sh53.6 billion in 2013 to Sh 97.6 billion this financial year. He said Kenyans expect better services.